  <text>
    <body>
      <p>
        <pb n="1" facs="#f1"/>
        <lb corresp="#f1_l1" n="1" type="line"/>On the Composition of TEI
        <lb corresp="#f1_l2" n="2" type="line"/>The text is encoded in TEI PS,
        <lb corresp="#f1_l3" n="3" type="line"/>with one &lt;surface&gt; per page image
        <lb corresp="#f1_l4" n="4" type="line"/>and one &lt;zone&gt; per recognized line.
        <lb corresp="#f1_l5" n="5" type="line"/>Each line of text is wrapped in
        <lb corresp="#f1_l6" n="6" type="line"/>an &lt;ab&gt; element whose @facs
        <lb corresp="#f1_l7" n="7" type="line"/>attribute points back to the zone
        <lb corresp="#f1_l8" n="8" type="line"/>in the facsimile section.
        <pb n="2" facs="#f2"/>
        <lb corresp="#f2_l1" n="1" type="line"/>Workflow
        <lb corresp="#f2_l2" n="2" type="line"/>1. Drop a folder of page images
        <lb corresp="#f2_l3" n="3" type="line"/>2. Pick OCR language or auto
        <lb corresp="#f2_l4" n="4" type="line"/>3. Run OCR on N pages
        <lb corresp="#f2_l5" n="5" type="line"/>4. Inspect bounding boxes
        <lb corresp="#f2_l6" n="6" type="line"/>5. Export TEI/XML
        <lb corresp="#f2_l7" n="7" type="line"/>The output validates against
        <lb corresp="#f2_l8" n="8" type="line"/>the official tei_all mg schema.
      </p>
    </body>
  </text>
